INTERLAKE STEAMSHIP COMPANY, Appellant, v. CITY OF TOLEDO, Appellee. No. 7152. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. April 9, 1937. McKeehan, Merrick, Arter & Stewart, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellant. Martin S. Dodd, of Toledo, Ohio, for appellee.

Before SIMONS, MACK, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The decree below is affirmed for the reasons given in the memorandum opinion of the District Judge and upon the 'authority of the cases therein cited, including Northern Pacific Ry. Co. v. Duluth S. S. Co., 252 F. 544 (C.C.A.8), certiorari denied 248 U.S. 575, 39 S.Ct. 12, 63 L.Ed. 428. Cf. The Gloria, 286 F. 188 (D.C.N.Y.); U. S. v. National City Bank, 83 F.(2d) 236, 238, 106 A.L.R. 1235 (C.C.A.2) ; U. S. v. The Thekla, 266 U.S. 328, 340, 45 S.Ct. 112, 69 L.Ed. 313.
